      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You are absolutely right; generic platitudes like \"time heals everything\" often feel hollow and invalidating when you are still in the acute throes of grief. Many people would rather sit with the raw, unmanaged pain of their loss than force a smile or pretend everything is fine. If you can find a space where no one tries to fix the void, or where someone simply listens without offering solutions, that might be the only real help you are looking for.",
